  "text": "It has been suggested that intracellular antioxidants can be consumed by chronic H. pylori infection; indeed, BSES treatment for 4 weeks led to slightly increased GSH concentrations in H. pylori (+) subjects. MDA is a product of lipid peroxidation and an indicator of oxidative cell injury. MDA concentrations in the gastric mucosa were significantly higher in subjects with H. pylori (+) gastritis than in H. pylori (-) subjects and after H. pylori eradication. [CITATION_1] In our study, basal MDA concentrations in H. pylori (+) subjects were markedly higher than those in H. pylori (-) subjects, but the differences did not reach statistical significance (p=0.083). Interestingly, MDA concentrations decreased significantly after BSES treatment in both the H. pylori (+) and H. pylori (-) BSES groups.",
